    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as the clear engine of the offense. With an elite score of 83.29, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive park factor boost (+16%) and an aggressive lead-off spot against Houser, making him our primary target for production. Complementing him is **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.87), who remains a locked-in start despite a challenging dynamic platoon scenario; his elite xwOBA of 0.384 and favorable matchup against Bradley provide a high enough floor to anchor the middle of the order. Meanwhile, **Marcell Ozuna** (67.73) and **Miguel Vargas** (63.64) are high-leverage plays today, with both benefiting from projected wind-out conditions and solid hitting environments that elevate their raw projections.\n\nOur decision-making process was pushed to the limit at the final utility spots, specifically regarding **Kyle Tucker** and **Andy Pages**. Despite **Kyle Tucker** drawing a difficult assignment against deGrom, his base profile remains too high to bench, though the matchup drags his efficiency down to 57.75. **Nolan Schanuel** was the toughest exclusion from the starting nine; his score of 55.51 was competitive, but he ultimately ceded his spot to the higher-ceiling profiles of our core infielders and hot-hand options like **Heliot Ramos**, whose favorable park factor and platoon edge against Povich outweighed **Nolan Schanuel**\u2019s steady presence. We are tracking a 39% rain risk for **Jackson Merrill**, which adds a layer of volatility to his 58.08 projection; owners should keep an eye on weather reports, as a mid-game delay could shorten his effectiveness. Otherwise, we are avoiding **Brady House** and **Coby Mayo** as they currently lack the efficiency metrics needed to justify a start over the active lineup.",
